g.text: Operating system is something that drives as a communication between software and hardware.
It is Heart of any Operating System. It has following main 4 Taks to do:
Shell is language through which you talk to your operating system.
Shell Commands are way through which you talk to os.
- ls (To see all files and folders present)
- pwd (To see in what directory or folder you are currently)
- cd (to move from one folder into another or to change the directory or folder)
- cd .. (comes back to previous folder or directory)
- ls -ltr (list the details about the directories like owner of file, created time, users)
- vi fileName (create and write into the file)
- free -g (see storage usage of the system)
- nproc (To see how much cpu's are thier in your VM)
- top (to see all above info at once we use top command)
